The paper deals with the analysis and modeling of mobile user behavior in social networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI). It also discusses the need for future mobility models, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses real-world data and statistical analysis, which can be related to multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
